{"url": "https://www.ics.uci.edu/~ejw/authoring/redmond/adv_col_protocol/sld006.htm", "content": "\r\n<!--  Presentation generated by Internet Assistant for Microsoft PowerPoint 97 -->\r\n\r\n<HTML>\r\n<HEAD>\r\n<META HTTP-EQUIV=\"Content-Type\" CONTENT=\"text/html;charset=windows-1252\">\r\n<meta name=\"GENERATOR\" content=\"Microsoft Internet Assistant for Microsoft PowerPoint 97\">\r\n <TITLE>Mandatory Extensions in HTTP: Rationale</TITLE> \r\n</HEAD>\r\n\r\n<BODY     >\r\n\r\n<CENTER>\r\n<TABLE WIDTH=100%> \r\n     <TR> <TD WIDTH=100% ALIGN=CENTER>\r\n         <IMG SRC=\"img006.jpg\" usemap=\"#Objmap\" WIDTH=480 HEIGHT=360 BORDER=0>\r\n     </TD> </TR>\r\n     <TR> <TD WIDTH=100% ALIGN=CENTER>\r\n         <A HREF=\"sld001.htm\"><IMG SRC=\"first.gif\" BORDER=0 ALT=\"First\"></A>\r\n         <A HREF=\"sld005.htm\"><IMG SRC=\"prev.gif\" BORDER=0 ALT=\"Previous\"></A>\r\n         <A HREF=\"sld007.htm\"><IMG SRC=\"next.gif\" BORDER=0 ALT=\"Next\"></A>\r\n         <A HREF=\"sld024.htm\"><IMG SRC=\"last.gif\" BORDER=0 ALT=\"Last\"></A>\r\n         <IMG SRC=\"space.gif\" BORDER=0>\r\n         <A HREF=\"index.htm\"><IMG SRC=\"info.gif\" BORDER=0 ALT=\"Index\"></A>\r\n         <A HREF=\"tsld006.htm\"><IMG SRC=\"text.gif\" BORDER=0 ALT=\"Text\"></A>\r\n     </TD> </TR>\r\n</TABLE>\r\n<P>Slide 6 of 24</P>\r\n</CENTER>\r\n\r\n <CENTER><Font size=4> <STRONG> Notes:  </FONT></STRONG><HR SIZE=3></CENTER><P> <UL>\r\n3 new methods, especially replacements for DAV methods, seems wrong.\r\n</UL><UL>\r\nUse the approach being recommended by IETF for extending HTTP.\r\n</UL><UL>\r\n\r\n</UL><UL>\r\n(Actually, a PUT with a collection as the request-URI probably fails on a plain HTTP server???\r\n</UL><UL>\r\nIt definitely fails on a plain WebDAV server unless a Collection-Member header is present.\r\n</UL><UL>\r\nSo it might be OK to use PUT with Referential-Member header to add referential members.)</UL> </P> \r\n<!-- <UL>\r\n<H2>Mandatory Extensions in HTTP: Rationale</H2>\r\n</UL></P>\r\n<P><UL>\r\n<LI><H2>HTTP servers ignore unrecognized headers\r\n</H2>\r\n</UL><UL>\r\n<LI><H2>We want requests to fail if the server doesn\u2019t recognize DAV headers\r\n</H2>\r\n</UL><UL>\r\n<LI><H2>PUT, MOVE, and COPY are affected\r\n</H2>\r\n</UL><UL>\r\n<LI><H2>3 new methods vs. Mandatory Extensions</H2>\r\n</UL></P>\r\n<P>  -->\r\n</Body>\r\n</HTML>\r\n", "encoding": "Windows-1252"}